# Notifications

## Due Date Reminders
@label(due-reminders)

Tasks with a due date trigger a reminder notification.
The default reminder fires at 9:00 AM on the due date in the user's local timezone.
Users can add up to 2 additional reminders per task (e.g., 1 hour before, 1 day before).
The default reminder plus any additional reminders total at most 3 per task.

## Reminder Content

The notification title is the task's title.
The notification body shows the due date and the list name (e.g., "Due today - Work").
Tapping the notification opens the task detail view.

## Notification Settings
@label(notification-settings)

Users can disable reminders globally in Settings.
Users can disable reminders per list.
@see(lists@default-lists)

## Quiet Hours

Notifications are suppressed from 10:00 PM through 6:59 AM (local time) by default.
Users can customize or disable quiet hours in Settings.
